snippet.textDisplay:
During the recent Lunar New Year festivities, Falun Gong practitioners in Adelaide participated in several local events. They introduced Falun Gong (also known as Falun Dafa), raised awareness about the 20-year persecution in China, and collected signatures on a petition to stop the atrocities.

Talking to People in Chinatown
From the first to the 15th day of the Lunar New Year, practitioners went to Chinatown on three consecutive weekends to wish people a Happy New Year and introduce the practice.

They set up an information booth and distributed handwritten Chinese calligraphy, New Year calendars with information about Falun Gong, and hand-made folded paper lotus flowers.





During the Chinese New Year, practitioners introduced Falun Gong in Adelaide's Chinatown.

A young man from Wuhan, China stopped at the Falun Gong booth. He had joined the Chinese Communist Party in high school when he was 18. Being from Wuhan, where the coronavirus first appeared, he is worried that his parents might contract the virus. Practitioners suggested he talk to them and tell them that Falun Gong is good and that the Chinese government has spread lies to instigate hatred of the practice. The man asked for the website address where he could learn more about Falun Gong.

He took photos of all the information boards, saying that he would read them carefully at home. He asked several questions and then renounced his Communist Party membership.

snippet.textDisplay:
As A Polyglot And Linguist, I Can Assure You That English Is Not An Easy Language. Not Even For An Alabama Boy Like Mr. Wilder Who Is Very Aware Of The Constant Criticism Of His Speech, Appearance, Philosophy, Etc., By Some Of Those In The Dominant Society.

Finding The Right Words To Say Whilst Being Hyper-Scrutinized Is A Tough Thing In Any Language!

Propers To Wilder For Rising Above The Fray, Sharing With Us His Positive Attitude And Message And Holding Down The Heavyweight Belt For The U.S.A.

I Personally Know 2 Entertainers, One From Tennessee, One From Texas; That Have Taken Speech Classes To "Get Rid Of" The Country 'Twang' In Their Diction.
Lol! Even Our "All About That Bass" American-Songwriter Meghan Trainor From Nantucket, MA Had To Do The Same!

I Didn't Get Why Americans Were Not Rooting For The American Fighter Who Has Won A Bronze Medal For Our Country. It Is As Befuddling As The Mayweather VS McGregor Fight. Why Was The Foriegn Fighter Favored, And The Undefeated Professional Boxer And American Bronze Olympian Disparaged?

Through Logic And Deductive Reasoning; I Am Certain That I Have Found The Undisclosed Answer.

Let Us Raise Up Our Fellow Americans..Our Countrymen!
Let Us Not Choose To Be Disparaging And Belittling Over The Proper Use Of The Words 'Was' And 'Were' When The Fact Is That There Are Many American Dialects From 'Appalachian' To 'Valley' To The Good Old 'North Boston' Dialect.

May We Appreciate And Learn From What Is Being Said And Not Miss The Message Because Of Over-Analysis And Overwhelmingly Unnecessary Dissection Of Speech.

In Closing, Both Of These Lads Are Indeed NOT Linguists. Do Note, Mr. Fury Does Vacillate From Mostly Chav To A Wee Bit Posh When He Needs To. We Must Also Keep In Mind That They Are Professional Boxers And That They Are Probably Closer Acquaintances Than We May Know Or WANT To Believe.

Let Us Not Place OUR Limitations And Digressions On Each Other; Be It Mr. Wilder's Speech Patterns Or Mr. Fury's Illegal Drug Abuse.
Let's Be Exited That These Two Heavyweights, Both Once Contemplating Suicide, Are Still With Us And Can Provide Us With Some Happiness In Our Own Lives.

Have A Great Fight Lads!!
May The Best Chap Win!
Cheers!!🥂
Cheers To The Game!!🍻
